2026-04-30T11:11:39.3934691Z               "message": "Replace CanIssue with IsAdmin; add admin config screen + per-domain DKIM\n\nAuth refactor:\n- AuthService.User.CanIssue → IsAdmin throughout (service, web endpoints,\n  tokens.html). Issue API param/JSON renamed to isAdmin.\n- Backward-compat: existing users.json files with \"canIssue\":true are\n  migrated transparently on Load() (covered by a new test).\n- /api/auth/me, /api/auth/users, /api/auth/login responses now expose\n  isAdmin (callers using the old canIssue field will see false until they\n  migrate).\n\nNew ConfigService + config.json:\n- Persisted at {dataDir}/config.json alongside cache/ and auth/.\n- On first run, seeded from env-var defaults + DkimSelectorsCheck.CommonSelectors\n  so behavior matches the previous build out of the box. After that the\n  file is the source of truth.\n- Schema:\n    { enableSmtpProbes, enableHttpProbes, enableDnsbl,\n      defaultDkimSelectors: [...],\n      dkimSelectors: { \"domain.com\": [\"sel1\", \"sel2\"] } }\n- New endpoints (admin-only): GET /api/config, PUT /api/config.\n- New /config.html admin page (gated in middleware) with a form view\n  (checkboxes + per-domain table) and a raw-JSON tab.\n\nDKIM precedence (DkimSelectorsCheck):\n  1. ForceDkimSelectors=true with user-supplied list → user list wins\n     (overrides per-domain config; merged with AXFR if any).\n  2. Per-domain config entry for the domain → use that.\n  3. User-supplied AdditionalDkimSelectors (+ AXFR) → use that.\n  4. AXFR-discovered selectors → use those.\n  5. Built-in CommonSelectors → fallback.\n\nValidationOptions adds:\n  • PerDomainDkimSelectors (Dictionary<string, List<string>>)\n  • ForceDkimSelectors (bool, default false)\n\nWeb UI:\n- index.html: new \"Force these selectors for every domain\" checkbox; live\n  hint shown under the DKIM field when the entered domain has a per-domain\n  config entry. Admin nav link to /config.html visible only to admins.\n- tokens.html: \"Can issue tokens\" checkbox renamed to \"Admin\"; row column\n  renamed; nav exposes /config.html for admins.\n- /api/defaults now returns the live config-driven default list plus the\n  per-domain map so the validator UI can show per-domain hints without a\n  separate fetch.\n\nGET /api/validate/{domain} also accepts ?forceDkimSelectors=true to mirror\nthe UI checkbox via query string.",
